The paper deals with the analysis of the outage capacity of a wireless network, which involves the study of information theory, networking, and optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves the modeling of user locations using a Poisson point process, which falls under the category of network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the scaling behavior of the beam outage capacity, which involves the use of mathematical analysis and asymptotic techniques, falling under the category of mathematical analysis (cs.MA). The paper also discusses the impact of path loss models on the beam outage capacity, which involves the use of game theory and optimization techniques, falling under the category of game theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper also discusses the applicability of the results to practical scenarios, which involves the use of simulation and experimental techniques, falling under the category of systems and control (cs.SI).
